Description: A ground-breaking global rating and age classification system for digitally delivered games and apps.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Administered by many of the world's game rating authorities, the International Age Rating Coalition (IARC) provides a globally streamlined age classification process for digital games and mobile apps, helping to ensure the consistent cross-platform accessibility of established, trusted age ratings by today's digital consumers. Established in 2013, IARC simplifies the process by which developers obtain age ratings by having them answer a single set of questions about their product's content and interactive elements. Their responses automatically generate different age ratings from each participating territory along with a generic rating for the rest of the world. IARC rating assignments also include content descriptors and interactive elements identifying apps that collect and share location or personal information, enable user interaction or share user-generated content, and/or offer in-app digital purchases. The IARC system currently includes the participation of rating authorities, which collectively represent regions serving approximately 1.5 billion people with more expected to participate in the future.

Description: ReEntry Capital is a venture capital firm.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: ReEntry Capital is a pioneering venture capital firm and accelerator program specifically aimed at supporting and empowering justice-involved founders. Born out of the founder's own experience with the justice system, ReEntry Capital seeks to bridge the resource gap for these entrepreneurs and challenge societal biases. Our approach centers on backing startups founded by individuals who have been impacted by the justice system. We believe that their unique insights, resilience, and creativity make them poised for success, and we're dedicated to giving them the support they need to unlock their full potential. Our focus spans across various sectors, fostering innovation and driving positive social impact. The ReEntry Capital Accelerator program provides intensive mentoring, resources, and support to enable these founders to transform their ideas into reality. Post-acceleration, ReEntry Capital also offers a fund to further support these startups, helping them scale and thrive in their respective markets. Our long-term goal is to challenge and change the narrative around justice-involved individuals. By supporting their entrepreneurial journey, we aim to demonstrate the untapped potential within this often overlooked population and encourage more inclusive entrepreneurship ecosystems. In addition to our accelerator and fund, ReEntry Capital is also committed to advocacy and education. We work to raise awareness about the systemic barriers justice-involved individuals face and promote policies and practices that support their reintegration into society. By combining venture capital with social impact, ReEntry Capital is working to create a more equitable entrepreneurial landscape. Lastly, ReEntry Capital is also exploring strategic partnerships and initiatives that align with our mission.

By forging strong partnerships with telemarketing and digital marketing entities, we have created an ecosystem that empowers customers and optimizes their solar experience. Through our state-of-the-art software solutions like SOLARIT A.I., SolarPro™, and CanvassPro™, combined with our strategic marketing partnerships, we are revolutionizing the way solar energy solutions are delivered and accessed. Our vision is to not only provide exceptional solar products and services but also to offer a seamless and customer-centric experience from the very first point of contact. Join SOLARIT® in shaping the future of solar energy and marketing partnerships. Visit SOLARIT.ORG today to learn more about our smart solar solutions and how we can collaborate to make a sustainable difference. Invest in the future of solar energy with SOLARIT®. Description: Opportunity Management Group (OMG) is a quickly growing sales & marketing firm committed to creating opportunities for growth & expansion.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Opportunity Management Group, open since March 2016, is a Charlotte based direct sales and marketing firm. We transform leaders into business owners by focusing on leadership development, management training, and communications coaching.  We partner with highly respected companies nationwide by offering them professionally trained sales teams to represent their brand, improve name recognition, and expand market reach.  But why wouldn't these firms just do their own sales? By outsourcing to Opportunity Management Group, they save time, money, and increase their profit margins.  Instead of focusing on recruiting, interviewing, hiring, etc their own sales team, Opportunity Management Group hires our own team. That alone saves our clients hours of work where they can reinvest that in creating a better product for us to market. This also saves our clients money they would have put into hiring and training new teams and allows them to spend that elsewhere or lower the cost of their product, also making it easier for us to sell (win win situation again). Lastly, our clients do not pay us unless we produce results. Working with Opportunity Management Group becomes a clear no brainer for our clients. Now how do we make working with our team a no brainer? We promise only internal advancement opportunities that will be given based on merit and by hitting clear targets. Description: Entest BioMedical develops immuno-therapeutic treatments that address illnesses and maladies in both veterinary and human medicine.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Entest BioMedical, Inc. engages in the development and commercialization of immunotherapeutic therapies for the veterinary market. The company is developing ImenVax family of canine cancer vaccines, which include ImenVax I, a therapeutic for canine cancer, which is involved in isolating tumor cells from the patient and placing the cells into a cell implant device that is inserted subcutaneously into the patient; ImenVax II that utilizes cell lines for sustained release of immunologically relevant cytokines for maximum anti-tumor immune responses; and ImenVax III, a canine cancer vaccine to treat existing tumors through stimulation of immune responses. It is also developing ENT-576 therapy for the treatment of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. In addition, the company operates veterinary hospitals. Entest BioMedical, Inc. was founded in 2008 and is based in La Mesa, California.
